It has long been known that the word frequency in language follows a power law distribution [25] which suggests that the embedding set generated from these words will also follow a power law distribution, especially in large documents. Given a centred word embedding set, a PCA to one dimension creates a linear projection such that the variance of the first principal component \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
